enger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cNo one should touch the Quran unless they are pure.\u201d Source: al-Mu\u2019jam al-Kabi\u0304r 13217 Grade: Hasan (fair) according to Al-Suyuti Ibn Abdul Barr said, \u201cAl-Shafi\u2019i, Al-Awza\u2019i, Abu Thawr, and Ahmad said the written Quran should\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":27566,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/04\/15\/permission-not-fast-journey\/","url_meta":{"origin":25304,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Travel: Permission to fast or not on journey, whatever is easiest","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"April 15, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: Hamzah ibn Amr asked the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, about fasting while traveling. The Prophet said, \u201cIf you wish, you may fast. And if you wish, you may break your fast.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 1841, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 1121 Grade: Muttafaqun Alayhi (authenticity agreed\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":38862,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2023\/02\/21\/imam-ahmad-dua-rulers\/","url_meta":{"origin":25304,"position":3},"title":"Ahmad on Rulers: Supplication for guidance of Caliphs and Imams","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"February 21, 2023","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Bakr al-Marrudhi reported: I heard Ahmad ibn Hanbal, may Allah have mercy on him, mentioning the Caliph al-Mutawakkil and he said, \u201cIndeed, I pray for his righteousness and well-being.\u201d Source: al-Sunnah li-Abi\u0304 Bakr al-Khalla\u0304l 16 \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u200c\u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0628\u064e\u0643\u0652\u0631\u064d \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0645\u064e\u0631\u064f\u0651\u0648\u0630\u0650\u064a\u064f\u0651 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0633\u064e\u0645\u0650\u0639\u0652\u062a\u064f \u0623\u064e\u062d\u0652\u0645\u064e\u062f\u064e \u0628\u0652\u0646\u064e \u062d\u064e\u0646\u0652\u0628\u064e\u0644\u064d \u0631\u064e\u062d\u0650\u0645\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u064f \u0648\u064e\u0630\u064e\u0643\u064e\u0631\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0652\u062e\u064e\u0644\u0650\u064a\u0641\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0645\u064f\u062a\u064e\u0648\u064e\u0643\u0650\u0651\u0644\u064e\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25503,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/12\/01\/bismillah-begin-salat\/","url_meta":{"origin":25304,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Bismillah: Reciting name of Allah to begin prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 1, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, as well as Abu Bakr and Umar, may Allah be pleased with them, would open the prayer by reciting, \u201cAll praise is due to Allah.\u201d (1:1) In the narration of Muslim, Anas said: I did not hear any of them\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":4098,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/08\/04\/ahmad-sunnah-tafseer-quran\/","url_meta":{"origin":25304,"position":5},"title":"Ahmad on Tafsir: The Sunnah is exegesis, explanation of Quran","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 4, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Al-Fadl ibn Ziyad reported: I heard Ahmad Ibn Hanbal, may Allah have mercy on him, respond to a question on the opinion that the Sunnah overrules the Quran. Ahmad said, \u201cI do not dare say that. Rather, the Sunnah is the explanation of the Book and its clarification.\u201d Source: al-Bah\u0323r\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/quran-exegesis-tafsir\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/25304","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/3712"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=25304"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/25304\/revisions"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=25304"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dai